text.en_US: You need to not be dashing right BEFORE you land on that floor to not fall off.
But you need 2 dashes to get on it!
How do you stop yourself from dashing?
No place to hit those switches from higher up...
Well, you do get a bit of height when you jump...
You passed the basic Long Jumps room!
Things are only just getting started though.
These tricks are getting more complicated and more unintuitive.
Signs with a "?" hovering over them will provide a hint as to what to do.
You can avoid reading them if you want to figure out the trick for yourself though.
However, the hints will not outright tell you how to progress!
Enjoy a fresh meal of hedgehag whenever you want though.
Don't overthink it.
This jump is simpler than it appears.
You're getting pretty good now!
It's time to step this up a notch now that we can guard.
Have you noticed that you can't move for a brief period after you dash?
If you tap guard for a split second after you dash you can cancel that end lag!
Without it, you won't have enough time to get past this next barrier.
Keyboard players can dash a different direction on this jump.
Sometimes you have to relearn the muscle memory for the second jump.
Remember, it's two dash inputs right before the melee input!
Try practicing starting at the end and work your way backwards to the beginning too.
